%% Failure recovery: SQS visibility-timeout redelivery
%% Applies to StateAggregator, IntervalReader, IntervalPublisher
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant P as Producer<br/>(StreamConsumer or IntervalAggregator)
    participant Q as SQS Queue
    participant C as Consumer<br/>(StateAggregator / IntervalReader / IntervalPublisher)
    participant T as Target<br/>(DynamoDB / external WFM)
    participant DLQ as Dead-Letter<br/>Queue

    P->>Q: SendMessage M1

    C->>Q: ReceiveMessage (long poll)
    Q-->>C: M1, visibility timeout starts (e.g. 60s)

    C->>T: process + write/POST
    T-->>C: ERROR (transient)
    C-->>C: throw exception

    Note over Q: Message NOT deleted<br/>Visibility timeout expires
    Q-->>Q: M1 visible again

    C->>Q: ReceiveMessage
    Q-->>C: M1 (attempt 2)
    C->>T: retry
    T-->>C: SUCCESS
    C->>Q: DeleteMessage M1

    Note over P,DLQ: Or - poison message:
    P->>Q: SendMessage M2 (malformed)

    loop receiveCount < maxReceives (e.g. 5)
        C->>Q: ReceiveMessage
        Q-->>C: M2
        C->>T: process
        T-->>C: ERROR (persistent)
        C-->>Q: visibility timeout, redelivery
    end

    Q->>DLQ: Move M2 to DLQ (alarm on DLQ depth)
